Types of ELB?
--------------
Four Types
1.Application load balancer (ALB):
Layer 7, best for HTTP/HTTPS apps

used for:
-Websites
-APIs
-Micro-services
-Kubernetes ingress
-Containers(ECS/EKS)

Works at Layer 7
-URL path(/login, /payment)
-Hostnames (api.company.com)

Example: Micro services app:
1. /login -----> Server A
2. /api -------> Server B
3. /admin ------> Server C


Real Time Example 1: E - Commerce website (Amazon/Flipkart style)
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Users--->Route 53 ---> ALB ----> EC2 Autosaling ----> RDS

Sceario:
---------
During Big Billion Day Sale, 5 Lakh users open website.

Without ELB:
------------
-One server gets overlaoded
-website crashes
-Slow checkout

With ALB:
----------
-Traffic Distributes across many EC2 servers
- /Products goes to app servers
- /Payment goes to payment service

If one server dies, remove automatically add new server automatically by EC2 autoscaling


2.Network load balancer(NLB):
Layer 4, best for TCP/UDP performance

3.Gateway Load balancer(GWLB):
Layer 3/4, best for security applications

4.Classic Load Balancer(CLB):
Layer 4/7 , older generation






